strings: Check SD card... Don't remove the SD card.
There is no SD card in SD card slot. Turn off the system and insert the SD card.
Unknown sd card. Shut down the system, remove the SD card, and then insert it again.
The SD card is write-protected. Turn off the system, slide the security switch to the unlocked position, and replace the SD card.
There is no image in the SD card. Whether you're in town, in a cave, or in a field, press START and take a photo.
The memory card does not contain any data. Go back to the title screen and generate the data.
There is not enough free space on the SD card. Please turn off the power and delete unnecessary data.
At the time of this writing, the SD card has been removed. Turn the system off and reinsert the SD card.
An error occurred while writing to the SD card. End the operation and re-insert the SD card.
Data on SD cards are no longer corrupted. Return to the main screen to read more data.
This app doesn't provide further details about the SD card, it returns to the main screen and adds more information.
This story could not be repeated without more information. Photos taken during the game and postcards received from other players are saved as additional information.
No other data under this title has yet been created on this SD card.
Other data is damaged. Titles cannot be played without additional processing of data.
SD cards created by other systems or on the SD card itself will show detailed information. This extension is unavailable.
If the attached data is overwritten, you will not be able to view captured images or received postcards. what am i doing
